        "## Workflow 3: CLIP + VAE Objects\n\n### What Changed\n\nTwo new isolated nodes are connected, and they receive **complex framework objects** from the host:\n\n- **CLIPTextEncode_ZIMG** receives CLIP from host CLIPLoader\n- **VAEDecode_ZIMG** receives VAE from host VAELoader and outputs IMAGE to host SaveImage\n\nThe host’s CLIP and VAE objects cannot be pickled or serialized as data. They are large, stateful PyTorch models.\n\n### What Crosses the Process Boundary\n\n**CLIP** and **VAE** — as lightweight proxy references.\n\nThe real objects stay on the host. The child gets `CLIPProxy` and `VAEProxy` objects that forward method calls back to the host via RPC.\n\n### Proxy Pattern\n\n```\nHost Process           Child Process\n──────────────         ───────────────\nCLIP (real obj)        CLIPProxy\n  │                        │\n  │── tokenize() ────────┘\n  │── encode() ──────────┘\n  (RPC callbacks)\n```\n\nThe child calls `clip.tokenize(text)` on its proxy. The proxy sends an RPC request to the host, the host executes on the real CLIP model, and sends the result back.\n"
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#000"
    },
    {
      "id": 84,
      "type": "MarkdownNote",
      "pos": [
        561.9523716308595,
        1026.0364172790512
      ],
      "size": [
        510,
