      "title": "Code from custom node",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "## Code: CLIP + VAE Proxies\n\n### Serialization (`comfy/isolation/adapter.py`)\n\nCLIP and VAE are registered as remote-handle types:\n\n```python\n# In ComfyUIAdapter.register_serializers()\nregistry.register(\n    'CLIP',\n    serialize_clip,      # obj → CLIPRef\n    deserialize_clip,    # CLIPRef → CLIPProxy\n    data_type=False,     # remote handle\n)\n```\n\n`data_type=False` means the object stays on the host. Only a lightweight reference dict crosses the wire.\n\n### Wire Format\n\n```json\n{\n    \"__type__\": \"CLIPRef\",\n    \"clip_id\": \"uuid-abc123\"\n}\n```\n\n### Proxy Implementation\n\n`comfy/isolation/clip_proxy.py`:\n\n- `CLIPProxy` — child-side RPC stub\n- `CLIPRegistry` — host-side real object store\n- Sub-proxies: `TokenizerProxy`, `CondStageModelProxy`\n\n`comfy/isolation/vae_proxy.py`:\n\n- `VAEProxy` — encode/decode forwarding\n- `VAERegistry` — host-side store\n- Sub-proxy: `FirstStageModelProxy`\n\n### Custom Node Code\n\nThe node code is unchanged — `clip.tokenize(text)` works transparently whether `clip` is real or a proxy.\n"
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#000"
    },
    {
